HEADWORD: Vexed
<hw>Vexed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Annoyed;
harassed; troubled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Much debated or contested; causing discussion;
<as>as, a <ex>vexed</ex> question</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Vexer</ent>⟦br⟧
